<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:TransactionDetails(CustomerPortal)-OutofScope">Out of Sc=
ope</h2>
<ul>
<li>Narrative generation solution</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"id-03.SD:TransactionDetails(CustomerPortal)-SolutionOverview"><sp=
an>Solution Overview</span></h1>
<p><span>Transaction Details allows a customer to view the details of a tra=
nsaction. On the screen a mixture of transaction data and payments data wil=
l be displayed for the related transaction.&nbsp; Transactions are related =
to Accounts contextually and can be either a debit or a credit while Paymen=
ts/Funds transfers relates to the payments sphere.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span>Account's data, such as transactions, are stored in ATLAS, while P=
ayment's data is stored in PODS. </span></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 72.=
5576%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 8.02671%;">
<col style=3D"width: 20.575%;">
<col style=3D"width: 6.61023%;">
<col style=3D"width: 64.6859%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"row" class=3D"confluenceTh">Context</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Type</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Data storage</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Data generation</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"row" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span>Accounts </span></th>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Transactions</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">ATLAS</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Events from 10X</li>
<li>Payment Events (needed for Narrative generation)</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"row" class=3D"confluenceTh">Payments</th>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Payments</p><p>Funds transfers</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>PODS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Events from 10X</li>
<li>Events from FIS</li>
<li>Events from Payment's APIs</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-03.SD:TransactionDetails(CustomerPortal)-Systems">Systems</h3>
<p>Included pages: <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/ATLAS+-+High-level">ATLAS - Hig=
h-level</a>, <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/PODS+High-level">PODS High-level</a><=
/p>
<p><strong>ATLAS (A016F9)&nbsp;</strong>(Accounts &amp; Transactions &amp; =
Ledger Aggregated Store) is an Operational Data Store modelling data from 1=
0x. It curates product, subscription and transactional data for consumption=
 by channels and for downstream integration for statements and other proces=
ses.</p>
<p><strong>PODS <span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">(A0154A)</span> </str=
ong>Payment Operational Data Store - <span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">=
FIS Payments stores payment history for only 28 days. The purpose for PODS =
is to ingest payment events from FIS to keep a long history and a fully rec=
onciled and persistent state for payments.</span></p>
<p>Services for data include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Payment status and history from FIS</li>
<li>Limited <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"8a0da3f8-2e59=
-4881-aba8-802b762c2a12">information from 10x (Enrich p</span>ayment inform=
ation)</li>
<li>Event matching and data reconciliation&nbsp;</li>
<li>End of Day posting to FAH and GL for NPP</li>
<li>Support audit, investigations and ad hoc customer enquiries</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
